WEBVTT

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
Four a.m. Thandi holds two things.

00:00:11.800 --> 00:00:15.500
Her daughter's hand — and her daughter's story.

00:00:18.600 --> 00:00:22.600
Six years of it, in a folder soft with handling.

00:00:24.800 --> 00:00:29.600
Somewhere on these shelves, her story waits. Or it doesn't.

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:36.000
So Thandi begins again.

00:00:40.300 --> 00:00:44.000
Paper doesn't just get lost. People do.

00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:50.500
What if the system remembered — so she never had to?

00:00:50.800 --> 00:00:56.000
This is C-H-I-S — the Centralised Health Information System.

00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:01.000
Tell it once. One record, made at the door.

00:01:03.600 --> 00:01:07.000
Every vital. Every visit. The whole story.

00:01:10.200 --> 00:01:13.000
The pharmacy already knows.

00:01:16.600 --> 00:01:20.000
The theatre is ready before she is.

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:27.000
And the whole facility, seen at a glance.

00:01:28.600 --> 00:01:35.000
No more lost files. No more missing history. When questions come, the record answers.

00:01:36.800 --> 00:01:42.500
One patient. One file — anywhere in South Africa that C-H-I-S runs.

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:47.500
No folder today. The story follows.

00:01:50.300 --> 00:01:57.000
One patient. One record. Every facility. A health system that remembers.
